15/05/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Representatives of the Bulgarian Drivers' Union (BDU) reached an agreement with its partners from the Balkan region to supply free roadside assistance to their members. 
BDU Chairman Georgi Yanakiev said Wednesday (14 May) that members would receive free aid when travelling in Macedonia, Greece, Romania and Serbia-Montenegro. 
Reciprocal service would be provided to members travelling in Bulgaria. 
The measure takes effect in June. 
(Dnevnik, Standart - 15/05/03)
